# Four monetization models work for large free user bases — each with different risk-return profiles
@type: comparison

@compare:
  header: Model | Conversion Rate Benchmark | ARPU | Risk | Best Fit
  row: Freemium (feature-gating) | 2–5% | $120–280/yr | Medium — requires product discipline | When power users are identifiable
  row: Usage-based / metered | N/A — all users pay | $80–600/yr (varies) | Low — natural alignment with value | When usage correlates with value
  row: Advertising (ad-supported) | N/A | $8–22/user/yr | Low — no conversion needed | When scale >10M MAU and content is attention-driving
  row: Marketplace / transactions | 0.5–2% of GMV take rate | Varies | Low — only successful transactions | When users transact with each other

@exhibit: Exhibit 1 — Monetization Model Comparison
@source: BCG Digital Monetization Benchmark, N=120 consumer platforms, 2024

@notes: The recommendation for this specific product is freemium + usage-based hybrid. Power users show clear willingness-to-pay signals; usage data supports value-based pricing.

