# Freemium architecture requires precise feature wall placement to maximize conversion
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## What Stays Free (Keeps Users)
  - Core value proposition that drove user acquisition
  - Social and community features creating network effects
  - Basic functionality covering 80% of casual use cases
  - Read-only or limited versions of power features

@col:
  ## What Gets Gated (Drives Conversion)
  - Features with proven power-user value (usage data confirms)
  - Collaboration and multi-user workflows
  - Export, API access, and integration capabilities
  - History, analytics, and insight features

@notes: The feature wall must be placed where users feel value, not frustration. Test extensively — a misplaced paywall destroys trust and drives churn, not conversion.

